@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
' @ref(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
'
' Objective-side flow for the `mdd render` command: the single
' deterministic engine rasterizes every renderable tree (models, cycle
' diffs, OCL, map, deploy, review-diff) to its .mdd/rendered/ mirror so
' the viewer (which has no PlantUML engine) can paint it. Invoked by
' /mdd-cycle's close step and by the /mdd-render thin-wrapper skill.
'
' @desc(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG, "How the `mdd render` mdd-cli command rasterizes the full tree set (models, cycle diffs, OCL, whole-map, deploy, review-diff) enumerated once by mdd-core Project to deterministic .mdd/rendered/ mirror paths. The cycle-close step and the /mdd-render thin-wrapper skill both invoke `mdd render` (no args = full parity; --only <trees> or explicit paths = subset); the skill adds only fuzzy subset intake, diagnostic triage, and fix suggestions.")
title Rasterize the renderable trees via `mdd render` (objective)

actor "Developer / CI" as Dev
participant "/mdd-cycle close\nor /mdd-render skill\n(thin wrapper)" as Trigger
participant "mdd render\n(mdd-cli subcommand)" as Cli
participant "mdd-core Project\n(single tree enumeration)" as Proj
participant "mdd-render engine" as Rend
database ".mdd/{models,cycles,constraints,\nmap,deploy,rendered/review}/**" as Store
participant "PlantUML jar\n(+ Graphviz dot)" as PUML
database ".mdd/rendered/**\n(deterministic mirror)" as Out

Dev -> Trigger : close cycle N  /  /mdd-render [fuzzy subset?]
note right of Trigger
  Skill judgment only: map "just the deploy
  diagrams" -> `mdd render --only deploy`.
  No mechanics here — it shells to the binary.
end note
Trigger -> Cli : `mdd render`  (or `--only <trees>` / explicit paths)
Cli -> Proj : enumerate the requested tree set
Proj --> Cli : source files (models, cycle diffs, OCL,\nwhole-map, deploy, review-diff)

loop each source file
  Cli -> Rend : render(source)
  Rend -> Rend : derive out = source path mirrored under .mdd/rendered/
  alt OCL source
    Rend -> Rend : synthesize constraints puml first
  end
  Rend -> PUML : plantuml -tsvg < puml
  alt render ok
    PUML --> Rend : svg
    Rend -> Out : write deterministic mirror path
  else dot/syntax diagnostic
    PUML --> Rend : diagnostic text
    Rend --> Cli : per-file diagnostic (hard failure -> non-zero exit)
  end
end
Cli --> Trigger : rendered list + diagnostics

opt diagnostics present
  Trigger -> Dev : triage + fix suggestion (skill judgment:\ninstall Graphviz, set MDD_PLANTUML_JAR, ...)
end
Trigger --> Dev : cycle N closed / subset rendered; SVGs available to the viewer

note over Out
  Every tree's output path is a pure mirror of its
  source (OCL-RENDER-PATH-MIRROR; the cycle case is
  OCL-DIFF-SVG-PATH-DERIVED). The tree set is the
  single mdd-core Project enumeration, never a
  second hand-maintained list (OCL-RENDER-TREE-PARITY).
  The viewer never invokes PlantUML; it only
  consumes these SVGs.
end note
@enduml
